Quick note: The clonotype information is difficult to work with and requires some assumptions. The first assumption was that we are selecting the TCR from A and B chains. The next assumption is simplifying the number of sequences down to the two top TCRA and TCRB hits, respectively.

Isolating TRA/TRB Contigs

We only want to look at TCR from the A and B chain, which is the vast majority of our clonotypes >97%

ALL <- list(P700, P744, P715,T700, T744, T715)
names <- c("P700", "P744", "P715","T700", "T744", "T715")

for (i in 1:length(ALL)) {
  testTRB <- subset(ALL[[i]], chain =="TRB")
  testTRA <- subset(ALL[[i]], chain =="TRA")
  testTRB <- testTRB[!duplicated(testTRB$barcode),]
  testTRA <- testTRA[!duplicated(testTRA$barcode),]
  DF <- rbind(testTRA, testTRB)
  assign(noquote(paste(names[i], "Final_filtered", sep = "_")),  DF)
}

Clonotype analysis by CD8 versus CD4 subtypes

CD8 Isolation

Here the code condenses the clonotypes by frequency for both peripheral and tumor CD8 T cells.

peripheral_names <- c("P700", "P744", "P715")

for (i in 1:length(peripheral)) {
  DF <- merge(peripheral[[i]], meta2, by = "barcode")
  DF <- subset(DF, CellType=="CD8")
  count <- DF[!duplicated(DF$barcode),]
  count <- as.data.frame(table(count$raw_clonotype_id))
  count <- subset(count, Freq > 0)
  count <- count %>%
    mutate(clonality = ifelse(Freq == 1, "One", ifelse(Freq == 2, "Two", "Greater3")))
  assign(noquote(paste(peripheral_names[i], "CD8clones", sep = "_")),  count)
}
  
tumor_names <- c("T700", "T744", "T715")
for (i in 1:length(tumor)) {
  DF2 <- merge(tumor[[i]], meta2, by = "barcode")
  DF2 <- subset(DF2, CellType=="CD8")
  count2 <- DF2[!duplicated(DF2$barcode),]
  count2 <- as.data.frame(table(count2$raw_clonotype_id))
  count2 <- subset(count2, Freq > 0)
  count2 <- count2 %>%
    mutate(clonality = ifelse(Freq == 1, "One", ifelse(Freq == 2, "Two", "Greater3")))
  assign(noquote(paste(tumor_names[i], "CD8clones", sep = "_")),  count2)
  
}
for (i in 1:length(tumor)) {
  DF <- merge(tumor[[i]], meta2, by = "barcode")
  DF <- subset(DF, CellType=="CD8")
  count <- DF[!duplicated(DF$barcode),]
  count <- as.data.frame(table(count$raw_clonotype_id))
  count <- subset(count, Freq > 0)
  count <- count %>%
    mutate(clonality = ifelse(Freq == 1, "One", ifelse(Freq == 2, "Two", "Greater3")))
  assign(noquote(paste(tumor_names[i], "CD8clones", sep = "_")),  count)
}

Clonotype Analysis

Modify as needed for patient ID - this will calculate the poportion of clonotypes with 1, 2 or greater than 3 repeated instances in the same patient.

#CD8
patients <- list(patient700, patient715, patient744)

for (i in 1:length(patients)) {
  dat <- patients[[i]]
  test <- subset(dat, data.ident == "0" | data.ident == "3" |data.ident== "6" |data.ident== "10" | data.ident == "17") 
  test <- test[!duplicated(test$barcode),]

  z <- as.data.frame(table(test$raw_clonotype_id))
  z <- subset(z, Freq > 0)
  z <- z %>%
    mutate(clonality = ifelse(Freq == 1, "One", ifelse(Freq == 2, "Two", "Greater3")))
  test <- merge(test, z, by.x="raw_clonotype_id", by.y="Var1")
  assign(noquote(paste("outCD8", i, sep = "_")),  test)
}
#CD4


for (i in 1:length(patients)) {
  dat <- patients[[i]]
  test <- subset(dat, data.ident == "1" | data.ident == "7" |data.ident== "12" | data.ident == "14" | data.ident == "21")  
  test <- test[!duplicated(test$barcode),]

  z <- as.data.frame(table(test$raw_clonotype_id))
  z <- subset(z, Freq > 0)
  z <- z %>%
    mutate(clonality = ifelse(Freq == 1, "One", ifelse(Freq == 2, "Two", "Greater3")))
  test <- merge(test, z, by.x="raw_clonotype_id", by.y="Var1")
  assign(noquote(paste("outCD4", i, sep = "_")),  test)
}

Counting the CD8 clonotypes

outputsCD8 <- list(outCD8_1, outCD8_2, outCD8_3)
outCD8 <- NULL

for (i in 1:length(outputsCD8 )) {
  dat <- outputsCD8[[i]]
  test <- dat[, c("raw_clonotype_id", "data.ident")]
  dTest <- dcast(test, raw_clonotype_id ~ data.ident)
  dTest <- dTest[apply(dTest[,-1], 1, function(x) !all(x==0)),]

    for (x in 2:6) {
      C0 <- length(which(dTest[,x] >= 1 & dTest[,2] >= 1))
      C3 <- length(which(dTest[,x] >= 1 & dTest[,3] >= 1))
      C6 <- length(which(dTest[,x] >= 1 & dTest[,4] >= 1))
      C10 <- length(which(dTest[,x] >= 1 & dTest[,5] >= 1))
      C17 <- length(which(dTest[,x] >= 1 & dTest[,6] >= 1))
      mat <- data.frame(C0, C3, C6, C10, C17)
      outCD8 <- rbind(outCD8,mat)
      assign(noquote(paste("outCD8_count", i, sep = "_")),  outCD8)
    }
  outCD8 <- NULL
}

Subtracting the extra counts for CD8 data

countsCD4 <- list(outCD4_count_1, outCD4_count_2, outCD4_count_3)

for (i in 1:length(countsCD4)) {
  df <- countsCD4[[i]]
    for (x in 1:5) {
      df[x,x] <- df[x,x] - (colSums(df[x])-df[x,x])
      rownames(df) <- colnames(df)
      
    }
  assign(noquote(paste("outCD4_count_v2", i, sep = "_")),  df)
  df <- NULL
}

Subtracting the extra counts for CD8 data

countsCD8 <- list(outCD8_count_1, outCD8_count_2, outCD8_count_3)

for (i in 1:length(countsCD8)) {
  df <- countsCD8[[i]]
    for (x in 1:5) {
      df[x,x] <- df[x,x] - (colSums(df[x])-df[x,x])
      rownames(df) <- colnames(df)
      if (df[5,5] < 0) {
        df[5,5] <- 0
      } else {
        df[5,5] <- df[5,5]
      }
        
      
    }
  assign(noquote(paste("outCD8_count_v2", i, sep = "_")),  df)
  df <- NULL
}

For looping to process CD8 clonotype information to find the mean

df <- matrix(, nrow = 5, ncol = 5)
for (x in 1:5) {
  col1 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,1], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,1], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,1])
  col2 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,2], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,2], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,2])
  col3 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,3], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,3], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,3])
  col4 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,4], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,4], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,4])
  col5 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,5], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,5], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD8_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,5])
  df[x,1] <- mean(col1)
  df[x,2] <- mean(col2)
  df[x,3] <- mean(col3)
  df[x,4] <- mean(col4)
  df[x,5] <- mean(col5)
  assign("CD8mean",  df)
}

For looping to process CD4 clonotype information to find the mean

df <- matrix(, nrow = 5, ncol = 5)
for (x in 1:5) {
  col1 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,1], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,1], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,1])
  col2 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,2], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,2], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,2])
  col3 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,3], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,3], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,3])
  col4 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,4], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,4], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,4])
  col5 <- c(prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_1), margin = 2)[x,5], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_2), margin = 2)[x,5], prop.table(as.matrix(outCD4_count_v2_3), margin = 2)[x,5])
  df[x,1] <- mean(col1)
  df[x,2] <- mean(col2)
  df[x,3] <- mean(col3)
  df[x,4] <- mean(col4)
  df[x,5] <- mean(col5)
  assign("CD4mean",  df)
}

Prepping CD4 Data for Chord Diagrams

list <- list(outCD4_count_v2_1, outCD4_count_v2_2, outCD4_count_v2_3)

for (x in 1:3) {
  df <- list[[x]]
  df[1,1] <- df[1,1]/2
  df[2,2] <- df[2,2]/2
  df[3,3] <- df[3,3]/2
  df[4,4] <- df[4,4]/2
  df[5,5] <- df[5,5]/2
  df <- as.matrix(df)
  df = data.frame(from = rep(rownames(df), times = ncol(df)),
    to = rep(colnames(df), each = nrow(df)),
    value = as.vector(df),
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
  df<- df[-c(4:6,8:10,14,15,24),]
  assign(noquote(paste("outCD4_chord", x, sep = "_")),  df)
}

Top CDR3 Amino Acid Sequences

CD4 T Cluster 21

Patients <- list(patient700, patient715, patient744)
Patients_names <- c("patient700", "patient715", "patient744")

for (i in 1:length(Patients)) {
  DF <- subset(Patients[[i]], data.ident==21)
  z <- as.data.frame(table(DF$raw_clonotype_id))
  test <- merge(DF, z, by.x="raw_clonotype_id", by.y="Var1")
  test <- test[order(test$Freq, decreasing = TRUE),]
  CDR3 <- head(unique(test$cdr3),3)
  Freq <- head(unique(test$Freq),3)
  count3 <- cbind.data.frame(CDR3, Freq)
  assign(noquote(paste(Patients_names[i], "Cluster21", sep = "_")),  count3)
}
X <-ggplot(patient700_Cluster21, aes(y=Freq, x=reorder(CDR3, Freq))) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="#F0C251", color="black", lwd=0.25) + 
  coord_flip() +
  theme_classic()+ 
  theme(axis.title = element_blank())

Y <-ggplot(patient715_Cluster21, aes(y=Freq, x=reorder(CDR3, Freq))) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="#A43D2B", color="black", lwd=0.25) + 
  coord_flip() +
  theme_classic() + 
  theme(axis.title = element_blank())

Z <-ggplot(patient744_Cluster21, aes(y=Freq, x=reorder(CDR3, Freq))) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="#7093E6", color="black", lwd=0.25) + 
  coord_flip() +
  theme_classic()+ 
  theme(axis.title = element_blank())

plot_grid(X,Y,Z, ncol=3)

ggsave("CD4_Cluster21_Top3clonotypes.pdf", height=2.5, width=8)
